To examine the transfer of annotated genomes across the air–sea interface, we compared relative abundances in bulk seawater, SSML, and SSA. The relative enrichment occurring in the sea-to-air exchange process was determined by calculating the aerosolization factor (AF) for each genome in the 0.2–3 µm size fraction for bacteria and 0.025–0.2 µm for viruses. This is defined as the ratio of the fraction in SSA (A) to the fraction in bulk seawater (B) or the fraction in the SSML (S) (Eq. 1). Surface enrichment factors are calculated similarly using the ratio of S to B (S:B).1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
